The paper discusses the task of semantic code search, which involves retrieving relevant code given a natural language query. This task involves bridging the gap between the language used in code and natural language, which is a common theme in information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the methodology used to obtain the corpus and expert labels, which involves techniques from software engineering (cs.SE) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI).
